"title": "5496: revenge, examples of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5496: revenge, examples of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Ungodly people are often vengeful, and even Christians are not always exemplary in this respect. However, each case should be considered on its merits, and the claims of justice taken into account.</p>\n<h2>Revenge among the ungodly</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:11\">LUK 6:11</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:14\">MAT 12:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:6\">MRK 3:6</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:24\">GEN 4:24</a> <em>Compare Lamech's words with those of Jesus Christ in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:21-Matt18:22\">Mt 18:21–22</a></em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:2\">1KI 19:2</a> <em>Jezebel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:27\">1KI 22:27</a> <em>Ahab</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:6\">EST 3:6</a> <em>Haman</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek25:15\">EZK 25:15</a> <em>the Philistines</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:19\">MRK 6:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:24\">MRK 6:24</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:33\">ACT 5:33</a> <em>the Sanhedrin</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:12\">ACT 23:12</a> <em>unbelieving Jews</em></p>\n<h2>Revenge among God's people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:4-Judg8:9\">JDG 8:4–8:9</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth9:1\">EST 9:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth9:5\">EST 9:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:5-Gen16:6\">GEN 16:5–16:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:30\">GAL 4:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:28-Judg16:30\">JDG 16:28–16:30</a> <em>Samson</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:10-1Sam25:13\">1SA 25:10–25:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam10:4-2Sam10:7\">2SA 10:4–10:7</a> <em>David did not retaliate at once, but only when a military threat appeared</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:27\">2SA 3:27</a> <em>Joab</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:51-Luke9:56\">LUK 9:51–9:56</a> <em>James and John</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:10-John18:11\">JHN 18:10–18:11</a> <em>Peter</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:2-Acts23:5\">ACT 23:2–23:5</a> <em>Paul</em></p>\n<h2>Examples of non-retaliation</h2>\n<h3>By Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:23\">1PE 2:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:6-Isa50:7\">ISA 50:6–50:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:7\">ISA 53:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:34\">LUK 23:34</a></p>\n<h3>By David</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:1-1Sam24:12\">1SA 24:1–24:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:11-Ps35:14\">PSA 35:11–35:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:17\">PSA 35:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:12-Ps38:15\">PSA 38:12–38:15</a></p>\n<h3>By others</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:15-Gen50:21\">GEN 50:15–50:21</a> <em>Joseph</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:23\">1SA 12:23</a> <em>Samuel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:24-1Kgs22:25\">1KI 22:24–22:25</a> <em>Micaiah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:29\">JOB 31:29</a> <em>Job</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:59-Acts7:60\">ACT 7:59–7:60</a> <em>Stephen</em></p>\n<h2>Expressions of desire for revenge</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps28:4\">PSA 28:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:8-Ps109:14\">PSA 109:8–109:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps137:8-Ps137:9\">PSA 137:8–137:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:15\">JER 15:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:21\">JER 18:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:8-Gal1:9\">GAL 1:8–1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:12\">GAL 5:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:10\">REV 6:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:5-Rev16:7\">REV 16:5–16:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:6\">REV 18:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:20\">REV 18:20</a></p>",
